<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Bootstrap Directory Structure</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        .folder {
            background-color: #f8f9fa;
            border: 1px solid #dee2e6;
            border-radius: 4px;
            padding: 15px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        .file {
            margin-left: 20px;
            color: #495057;
        }
        .purpose {
            background-color: #e9ecef;
            padding: 10px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            margin-top: 10px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Bootstrap Directory Structure</h1>
    
    <div class="folder">
        <h2>bootstrap/</h2>
        <p>This is the root directory of the downloaded Bootstrap package.</p>
        
        <div class="folder">
            <h3>css/</h3>
            <div class="file">bootstrap.min.css</div>
            <div class="file">bootstrap.css</div>
            <div class="file">bootstrap-grid.min.css</div>
            <div class="file">bootstrap-grid.css</div>
            <div class="file">bootstrap-utilities.min.css</div>
            <div class="file">bootstrap-utilities.css</div>
            <div class="file">bootstrap-reboot.min.css</div>
            <div class="file">bootstrap-reboot.css</div>
            
            <div class="purpose">
                <strong>Purpose:</strong> Contains all CSS files for Bootstrap. The minified versions (.min.css) are for production use, 
                while the unminified versions are for development. The grid, utilities, and reboot files are 
                optional partial distributions.
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="folder">
            <h3>js/</h3>
            <div class="file">bootstrap.bundle.min.js</div>
            <div class="file">bootstrap.bundle.js</div>
            <div class="file">bootstrap.min.js</div>
            <div class="file">bootstrap.js</div>
            
            <div class="purpose">
                <strong>Purpose:</strong> Contains all JavaScript files. The bundle versions include Popper.js (required for dropdowns, 
                popovers, and tooltips). The non-bundle versions require Popper.js to be included separately.
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="folder">
            <h3>icons/</h3>
            <div class="file">bootstrap-icons.css</div>
            <div class="file">fonts/ (contains icon font files)</div>
            
            <div class="purpose">
                <strong>Purpose:</strong> Contains Bootstrap Icons (if included). This is a separate icon library that can be used with 
                Bootstrap. It provides scalable vector icons that can be easily customized with CSS.
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <h2>Typical Project Structure When Using Downloaded Files</h2>
    <pre>
project-root/
├── css/
│   └── bootstrap.min.css       # Minified Bootstrap CSS
├── js/
│   ├── bootstrap.bundle.min.js # Minified Bootstrap JS with Popper
│   └── popper.min.js           # Only needed if not using bundle version
└── index.html                  # Your HTML file
    </pre>
</body>
</html>
